724409f-b.title: Manhattan: West Broadway - Spring Street
724409f-b.text:
West Broadway, north from a point slightly to the
south of Spring Street and across same, showing mainly
the easterly side of this thoroughfare.
In the foreground appears a truck loaded with
either industrial waste cotton or scrap paper.
At the right are several low structures that were
purchased by the Cranford Holding Co. from Mrs. Leslie
and who now have a plot of 10,O00 square feet here. This
was reported by the New York Times of October 20, 1937.
The two 2y-story buildings (No's 395 and 397) that fomaarly
adjoined have been demolished and the first replaced by
a garage.
May 19, 1939
Views 1, 2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
